<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Characteristic Species</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Calamagrostis</i> <i>nutkaensis</i> is dominant or co-dominant in the herbaceous layer with <i>Anthoxanthum</i> <i>odoratum</i>, <i>Artemisia</i> <i>suksdorfii</i>, <i>Elymus</i> <i>glaucus</i>, <i>Festuca</i> <i>arundinacea</i>, <i>Festuca</i> <i>rubra</i>, <i>Heracleum</i> <i>maximum</i>, <i>Holcus</i> <i>lanatus</i> and <i>Pteridium</i> <i>aquilinum</i>. Emergent trees and shrubs may be present at low cover, including trees <i>Picea</i> <i>sitchensis</i> and shrubs:<i>Baccharis</i> <i>pilularis</i>, <i>Gaultheria</i> <i>shallon</i>, <i>Rubus</i> spp., <i>Rubus</i> <i>ursinus</i> and <i>Vaccinium</i> <i>ovatum</i>. </div>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Vegetation Layers</h4>
	<div class="text">  Herbs < 1.5 m; cover is open to intermittent. </div>
</div>

        
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Membership Rules</h4>
	<ul class="text">
		
		<li><i>Calamagrostis nutkaensis</i> and other native perennial grasses > 15% relative cover in the herbaceous layer (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003a).</li>
		
		<li><i>Calamagrostis nutkaensis</i> > 50% relative cover in the herbaceous layer, or > 30% relative cover with <i>Baccharis pilularis</i> (Buck-Diaz et al. 2021, Sikes et al. 2021).</li>
		
	</ul>
</div>

        
	
<div class="allianceSection">
	 <h4 class="header">Habitats</h4>
	<div class="text"> Valley bottoms, lower portions of alluvial slopes, terraces, coastal bluffs. The USFWS Wetland Inventory (1996 national list) recognizes <i>Calamagrostis nutkaensis</i> as a FACW plant. </div>
</div>

        
